race.description: Mount Augustus Tourist Park Walkaway Cup
race.comment: TWILIGHT TALE (4) is a consistent mare who tried hard in her last start when closing strongly to finish third and just a length off the winner over 2200m at Ascot 3 weeks ago. She is nicely placed here, and from a good gate, she will be hard to hold out. GINGER GREEN (1) is a durable veteran who backs up quickly after a solid third at Ascot a week ago. He may not have won for some time, and is having his first run on this track, but he cannot be taken lightly. LONG GENES (5) was fourth in town last outing, when finishing under 3 lengths away from the winner. He won his penultimate start there before that, and he is spot on for this assignment. Can win. NOAHQUINTILLY (12) may not win often, but is usually thereabouts. She ran well last time, finishing fourth and just over a length from the winner over 2100m at Ascot a week ago. Stick with him. TRUEVINSKY (14) hasn't hit top form this prep, but has the pole position, and can spice up some top 4 combos here.
